{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust and fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. White-collar crimes of this nature require a sentence that provides general deterrence to others in similar positions of trust. However, several mitigating factors are heavily weighed in this sentencing: the defendant has no prior criminal record, showing this is an isolated lapse in judgment rather than a pattern of criminal behavior, and the defendant has already made a good-faith effort to partially repay the stolen funds. Balancing the need for accountability with the defendant's lack of criminal history and ongoing efforts toward restitution, a short period of incarceration is appropriate. This will be followed by a period of supervised release and an order to pay the remaining restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
